    <title>Hello World</title>
    <link href="/2025/09/25/hello-world/"/>
    <url>/2025/09/25/hello-world/</url>
    
    <content type="html"><![CDATA[<p>This blog tells the story about this personal website itself. Hope it would be helpful for you to create your own wiki 🙌 </p><h2 id="Log"><a href="#Log" class="headerlink" title="Log"></a>Log</h2><p>2025/9/25 build this website using <a href="https://hexo.io" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener"><span>Hexo</span></a> +  <a href="https://github.com/fluid-dev/hexo-theme-fluid" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener"><span>Fluid</span></a></p><h2 id="Tutorial"><a href="#Tutorial" class="headerlink" title="Tutorial"></a>Tutorial</h2><p>This also serves as a memo for me.</p><h3 id="Requirments"><a href="#Requirments" class="headerlink" title="Requirments"></a>Requirments</h3><p><strong>Linux</strong> is recommanded since it saves a lot of clicking around. If you haven’t used it before, don’t worry. Start off by trying <strong>WSL2 &amp; Ubuntu</strong> for Windows users. You’ll need to search related tutorials for yourself.</p><p>I refered to this blog <a href="http://karlzz.icu/2025/07/28/Hexo%20%E5%BB%BA%E7%AB%99%E6%95%99%E7%A8%8B/index.html">Hexo建站教程</a> to set up my environment. </p><p>It’s a well-organized tutorial but I still meet some trouble when executing <code>hexo init</code> – The git-clone process failed with time-out connection. So it’s <strong>strongly recommended</strong> to replace <code>hexo init</code> with</p><figure class="highlight bash"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre><span class="line">1</span><br><span class="line">2</span><br><span class="line">3</span><br></pre></td><td class="code"><pre><code class="hljs bash">$ git <span class="hljs-built_in">clone</span> https://gitee.com/hexojs/hexo-starter.git Hexo-Blog<br>$ <span class="hljs-built_in">cd</span> Hexo-Blog<br>$ npm install<br></code></pre></td></tr></table></figure><h3 id="Create-a-new-post"><a href="#Create-a-new-post" class="headerlink" title="Create a new post"></a>Create a new post</h3><figure class="highlight bash"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre><span class="line">1</span><br></pre></td><td class="code"><pre><code class="hljs bash">$ hexo new <span class="hljs-string">&quot;My New Post&quot;</span><br></code></pre></td></tr></table></figure><p>More info: <a href="https://hexo.io/docs/writing.html">Writing</a></p><h3 id="Run-server"><a href="#Run-server" class="headerlink" title="Run server"></a>Run server</h3><figure class="highlight bash"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre><span class="line">1</span><br></pre></td><td class="code"><pre><code class="hljs bash">$ hexo server<br></code></pre></td></tr></table></figure><p>This will produce a local site, usually at <code>localhost:4000</code>.</p><p>More info: <a href="https://hexo.io/docs/server.html">Server</a></p><h3 id="Generate-static-files"><a href="#Generate-static-files" class="headerlink" title="Generate static files"></a>Generate static files</h3><figure class="highlight bash"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre><span class="line">1</span><br><span class="line">2</span><br></pre></td><td class="code"><pre><code class="hljs bash">$ hexo clean<br>$ hexo generate<br></code></pre></td></tr></table></figure><p>More info: <a href="https://hexo.io/docs/generating.html">Generating</a></p><h3 id="Deploy-to-remote-sites"><a href="#Deploy-to-remote-sites" class="headerlink" title="Deploy to remote sites"></a>Deploy to remote sites</h3><figure class="highlight bash"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre><span class="line">1</span><br></pre></td><td class="code"><pre><code class="hljs bash">$ hexo deploy<br></code></pre></td></tr></table></figure><p>After deployment, it often takes several minutes to see the changes.</p><p>More info: <a href="https://hexo.io/docs/one-command-deployment.html">Deployment</a></p>]]></content>
    
    
    
